title: Want To Buy:  Mosin Nagants: Models 91/38, M91, 1895 Winchester 7.62x54R
postcontent:
The 91/38 looks just like an M38, however, it is a modification done by the Czechs. Every example I have seen of a model 91/38 has an imperial date on the barrel shank, and hex receiver. Prefer antique dated versions, but please email me with some info of one you may have! 

Model 1891 infantry rifle. Not looking for common 91/30s, the recent imports, or one you can regularly go to a Gander Mtn, Cabela's, Big 5 or local sporting goods store to find. I am looking for the original model 1891 antique dated on the barrel and receiver tang (dated 1898 or prior). The earlier the better, and earlier features the better. No import marks is a plus. May consider other years of M91 production, like 1919 Tula or pre 1909 dated M91s with early features. More matching the better, Finn capture OK too.

1895 Winchesters were produced for the Russians on contract by Winchester. They have a 5 round box mag, and are lever action. Looking ONLY for 1895s chambered in 7.62x54R Russian caliber that were contract rifles.

Shoot me an email with something you might have, and we can discuss price. Local FTF, otherwise out of state, I will pay for shipping. Don't really have anything to trade at this time.
